      code: "final class TtlDaemon implements Runnable {\n    private volatile boolean running = true;\n    public void stop() { running = false; }\n    public void run() { while (running) sweepExpiredKeys(); }\n}",
      questions: [["EASY", "What does volatile solve?", "Visibility and ordering for that variable."], ["MEDIUM", "Why not volatile for count++?", "count++ is read-add-write and needs atomicity."], ["HARD", "Why can GC kill latency?", "Stop-the-world phases pause application threads." ]],
